<br>
Druids should have had better heals from the get-go.  So giving them a 2000~ or so heal makes sense -- or made sense during RoK.  Shaman don't need better heals -- they were fine as is.  But druids needed something like this.<br>
<br>
The problem is now many encounters will be trivialized.  Much like the magic resist patches and AA skills trivialized certain encounters, the new healing spells will make things MUCH easier for latecomers (i.e. 2nd, 3rd, 4th tier guilds).<br>
<br>
As for Clerics getting screwed out of exp groups, well I for one don't see that happening. And if it does, tough shit honestly -- welcome to the world the rest of us face in exp groups.  The rest of us always had to fight our way into exp groups while clerics were coddled.  If you're really a good cleric and socially adept, you'll still get plenty of exp groups.  If not, you don't deserve a group anyway so go play Solitaire while you cancel your EQ account as my druid twink heals me.<br>
<br>
The truth is, druids should have had better heals since the day RoK went live.  That would have negated the *trivialization effect* that these kind of major balance changes have on the high end game.<br>
